ack\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Nov 06, 2023</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104kdb1665702780441.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/kdb1665702780441.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/kdb1665702780441.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"kdb1665702780441\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">Resize\n      Columns</h1>\n<div class=\"body taskbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">You can resize the width of columns by clicking the triangle in column header, and setting the desired width.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section context\" id=\"kdb1665702780441__context_w8481ab1b5b1_w8482ab1b5_w8483ab1\">In tools that contain columns, such as Component Structure Editor,\n         Resource Browser, and Properties Inspector, you can change the width of the\n         columns.</section>\n<section><ol class=\"ol steps\"><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"kdb1665702780441__li_d1367e1_d1368e1_d1369e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"kdb1665702780441__p_d3800e1_d3801e1_d3802e1\">Move the mouse cursor over the column header, then\n               click the Menu arrow.</span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<figure class=\"fig fignone\" id=\"kdb1665702780441__fig_adz_pcy_3zb\">\n<img alt=\"Menu indicator for columns\" class=\"image\" id=\"kdb1665702780441__image_o1j_qcy_3zb\" src=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/resizecolumn.png?_LANG=enus\"/>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"kdb1665702780441__p_d3803e1_d3804e1_d3805e1\">This displays a dialog box in which you can set the\n                  desired width of the column, as well as the minimum and maximum width.</p><figure class=\"fig fignone\" id=\"kdb1665702780441__fig_ffx_scy_3zb\">\n<img alt=\"Resize Column Dialog\" class=\"image\" id=\"kdb1665702780441__image_gfx_scy_3zb\" src=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/resizecolumndialog.png?_LANG=enus\"/>\n</figure>\n</div>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"kdb1665702780441__li_d1370e1_d1371e1_d1372e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd keypress\">Set the dimensions, in pixels, as desired, and press Enter.\n            </span>\n</li></ol></section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2529158\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2529158\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Resize Columns Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Nov 06, 2023 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Resize Columns You can resize the width of columns by clicking the triangle in column header, and setting the desired width. In tools that contain columns, such as Component Structure Editor, Resource Browser, and Properties Inspector, you can change the width of the columns. Move the mouse cursor over the column header, then click the Menu arrow. This displays a dialog box in which you can set the desired width of the column, as well as the minimum and maximum width. Set the dimensions, in pixels, as desired, and press Enter. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}